episodes.title: Alleged California 'cult' leaders arrested for member's murder
episodes.description:
We are learning more today about the group known as “His Way Spirit Led Assemblies” which has been under investigation since May 2023. Two members from the group, who are considered leaders, were arrested on suspicion of killing one of their members Thursday. This comes three years after the victim was last seen at a coffeehouse. According to police, Emilio Ghanem, 40, was reported missing shortly after leaving what is now being described as a “cult”.

episodes.title: Vegan cult murder: Death penalty sought in 'Zizians' killing case
episodes.description:
A member of the cult-like Zizians group made her first court appearance Friday for the killing of a US border agent after prosecutors announced they would seek the death penalty.

Teresa Youngblut pleaded not guilty to several charges including murder. She is accused of fatally shooting agent David Maland in Vermont on Jan. 20, the day of President Donald Trump’s inauguration.

Investigators said the 21-year-old is among a group of radical computer scientists who focused on veganism, gender identity and artificial intelligence. They have been linked to at least SIX killings in THREE states across the US, according to detectives.

Known as the Zizians, the group follows Jack LaSota, a transgender woman who goes by "Ziz," attracting young computer scientists who share anarchist beliefs.

episodes.title: BREAKING: Jay-Z accused of raping 13-year-old girl in a Diddy lawsuit  | LiveNOW from FOX
episodes.description:
Jay-Z was accused of raping a minor along with Sean "Diddy" Combs at a MTV VMAs after-party in 2000, according to documents obtained by Fox News Digital.

The lawsuit, which was initially filed in October, was refiled Sunday in New York by an anonymous accuser claiming Jay-Z, whose full name is Shawn Carter, "raped" her while Combs and "Celebrity B" watched.

Initially, the lawsuit stated Combs raped the minor while "Celebrity A" and "Celebrity B" watched. Carter was named as "Celebrity A" in the refiled lawsuit.
Combs and Carter allegedly "took turns assaulting the minor," according to the lawsuit. "Many others were present at the afterparty, but did nothing to stop the assault." 

The 13-year-old girl was dropped off at Radio City Music Hall by a friend as she wanted to attend the MTV Video Music Awards in 2000, according to a lawsuit. In an attempt to gain entry to the venue, she began approaching limousine drivers waiting outside the celebrity-filled event.
"One of the limousine drivers she spoke to claimed to work for [Diddy]," the lawsuit read. "He told her that Combs liked younger girls and said she ‘fit what Diddy was looking for,’ not allowing her into the Awards, but inviting her to an afterparty."
